<subSubSection id="B4B26EF3B02637677226FE2FFA9DFCAA" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FC173D78B02637677226FE2FFA9DFCAA" blockId="3.[804,1456,477,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="CEDCE16AB02637677226FE2FFC40FE0A" box="[842,899,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Notes</emphasis>
â A single collection was designated by Boissier (1867) in the protologue oF 
<emphasis id="CEDCE16AB0263767751CFE0FFA73FDE9" box="[1136,1456,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="3BA846FBB0263767751CFE0FFA6FFDE9" authority="Balansa 1312" authorityName="Balansa" authorityYear="1312" box="[1136,1452,509,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="splendens">S. splendens (Balansa 1312)</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This collection clearly corresponds to two gatherings, one (in flowers) collected on 
<date id="88161BB8B02637677559FDCCFB41FDAA" box="[1077,1154,573,597]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="2015-07">July 15</date>
and a second (in Fruits) on 
<date id="88161BB8B02637677248FDAFFC5BFD89" box="[804,920,606,630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="1917-08">August 17</date>
(
<figureCitation id="649321FDB026376772CBFDACFC2AFD89" box="[935,1001,605,630]" captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="3.[109,136,1308,1327]" captionTargetBox="[109,759,279,1293]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[107,760,278,1294]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. â Lectotype of Silene splendens Boiss. (designated by an arrow). [Balansa 1312, G-BOIS]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/162050/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Åese two gatherings have been widely distributed with a single label indicating both flowering and Fruiting dates. We consider that the most complete material is in flower and thereFore designate the specimen mounted on the leFt oF the First sheet at G-BOIS as the 
<typeStatus id="231383DAB0263767742BFD2CFA6DFD0A" box="[1351,1454,733,757]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="649321FDB02637677240FD0CFCAFFCE9" box="[812,876,765,790]" captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="3.[109,136,1308,1327]" captionTargetBox="[109,759,279,1293]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[107,760,278,1294]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. â Lectotype of Silene splendens Boiss. (designated by an arrow). [Balansa 1312, G-BOIS]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/162050/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). CareFul studies oF all material available allow separating the two gatherings in the relevant herbaria where the Fruiting material is designated as remaining 
<typeStatus id="231383DAB02637677597FCCFFA99FCAA" box="[1275,1370,830,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">syntypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
